  "prompt": "What should I gift to my teacher?",
  "response": "Choosing a gift for your teacher can be a thoughtful way to show appreciation for their hard work and dedication. Here are some ideas that might help:\n\n1. **Personalized Gifts**: Custom items like a mug, tote bag, or notebook with their name or a heartfelt message can be meaningful.\n   \n2. **Gift Cards**: A gift card to their favorite coffee shop, bookstore, or restaurant can be practical and appreciated.\n\n3. **Books**: Consider a book on a subject they love or a bestselling novel.\n\n4. **Handwritten Note**: A sincere note expressing your gratitude and sharing specific ways they\u2019ve impacted your life can be very touching.\n\n5. **Classroom Supplies**: Teachers often spend their own money on classroom supplies. Items like markers, pens, paper, or educational games can be very useful.\n\n6. **Plants**: A small potted plant can brighten up their classroom or home.\n\n7. **Subscription Services**: A subscription to a magazine, educational resource, or streaming service they might enjoy.\n\n8. **Homemade Treats**: If you enjoy baking, homemade cookies or brownies can be a sweet gesture.\n\n9. **Relaxation Items**: Consider a gift that promotes relaxation, like a scented candle, bath salts, or a cozy blanket.\n\n10. **Art Supplies**: If they enjoy art, high-quality supplies like paints, brushes, or sketchbooks can be wonderful.\n\nRemember, the most important aspect of the gift is the thought and appreciation behind it.",
